52.0	Dolley_Madison	Dolley Madison	Dolley Payne Todd Madison (May 20, 1768 â€“ July 12, 1849) was the spouse of the fourth President of the United States, James Madison, and was First Lady of the United States from 1809 to 1817. During the previous administration of Thomas Jefferson, a widower and their friend, she occasionally acted as First Lady to fulfill the ceremonial functions more usually associated with the President's wife. She was notable for her social gifts and is credited with helping define the role of the First Lady, as well as contributing to the popularity of Madison as president.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/Dolley_Madison.jpg/220px-Dolley_Madison.jpg
